Have you ever pulled a Regina George and asked this question?!? ‚òùÔ∏è‚òùÔ∏è‚òùÔ∏è

Nothing grinds my gears more than bogus nutrition info. ü§¨Lately what has been peeving me is the comparison of carrots to higher carb items like pretzels, bread, etc. üôÖ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏èThey are NOT the same!

Yes, carrots DO have carbs. You‚Äôd be correct. üëåBUT, they‚Äôre not interchangeable. Carrots don‚Äôt have the same amount of fueling energy as, say, pretzels do. ü•®The energy that our bodies and brains need and want. . 
Saying that carrots are a replacement for the real-deal carb items (talking pretzels, breads, etc) is like saying a cat üê±will be just fine for a dog personüê∂. Sure, they‚Äôre alike, but TOTES not the same- not as satisfying!
. 
Speaking from experience, if you skip the real-deal carbs there is a good chance you‚Äôll wind up in the pantry later on searching for chips, cookies, etc. to satisfy your bod. üç™üç∞üßÅLikely leaving yourself feeling stuffed and probs a little (or a lot) frustrated.üò¨
. 
Instead of fearing higher carb foods, work towards understanding hunger and fullness. üôåüèªThis is a HUGE piece of what I teach my clients how to do. Teach you how be able to sit down in front of an entire bag of pretzels and be able to know when to stop based on your body‚Äôs needs. It‚Äôs magical!ü§©ü¶Ñ

Social media makes it seem like food freedom is all about choosing the highest calorie, highet fat, highest sugar (etc. etc. etc) item...but is that really what you should do? ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏èLet me explain‚Ä¶.
. 
Honestly, I love both of these nogs. ‚òùÔ∏èThey both have a time and a place, in my opinion. It‚Äôs 180% OKAY to pick the almond nog if you want something lighter and this option satisfies you and doesn‚Äôt make you feel deprived. üëèBUT, if you‚Äôd be drinking the almond nog and think ‚ÄúThis tastes like watered down scrambled eggs‚Ä¶.‚Äù don‚Äôt drink it! üôÖ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏èGo for the real deal if that is what will leave you with a smile on your face!ü§©
. 
I always tell the girlfriends in my program to ask themselves this question: ‚ÄúHow would you feel if the real deal was the only option? Would you freak out or not have it?‚Äùüò¨
.
